    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-05T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-05T23:00:00-05:00" n="684"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.70/10–544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-06T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 6, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8188. For Hooker, Allison and Moats from Berle and Plakias.<note n="47"
                        xml:id="d684fn47">John N. Plakias, special assistant, Office of
                        Transportation and Communications.</note> Reference penultimate paragraph
                    Embassy’s 8366 October 5. Department feels same principle should govern
                    participation of Rumanian Control Commission at EITO Conference as applied to
                    ACC for Italy, SHAEF et cetera, namely, participation as observers only.</p>
                <p>However the Department feels that representation of Control Commission for
                    Rumania should await full establishment of the Commission and the naming by the
                    full Commission of a delegate as observer. <pb facs="0822" n="812"
                        xml:id="pg_812"/> (We have no objection in principle to the Soviet delegate
                    being this observer, but feel that the appointment should be made by the
                    Commission itself.) [Berle and Plakias.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
